Plots with ggplot2

We are going to make plots in R using the ggplot2 package from the tidyverse.

We will install these packages

  • tidyverse: suite of packages for wrangling & viz (ggplot)
  • readxl: to read in excel files (in many ways)
  • here: to help with filepaths
library(tidyverse) # install packages("tidyverse")
library(readxl) # install packages("readxl")
library(here) # install packages("here")

California National Parks Data

ca_np <- read_csv(here("data/ca_np.csv"))

Make my own first graph!

Here’s a smaller title

We’re going to make a line plot of year (x-variable) vs visitors (y-variable) in ggplot:

Command + option/alt + I

# Trying ggplot2 with Channel Islands

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) + 
  geom_area()

Update the geom_to geom_point(), geom_col(), geom_area()

Make a base layer for my CI plots:

gg_base <- ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors))

gg_base + geom_point()

Now let’s start customizing

  • Line / point colors: color
  • Change line type: linetype
  • Change point stype: pch
  • Change transparency: alpha
gg_base + 
  geom_line(
    color = "purple" , 
    linetype = "dashed"
  )

Activity: create a ggplot scatterplot (geom_point) that has triangle symbols (hint: ?pch), of non-default size (size = #), and that are an updated color.

gg_base + 
  geom_point(
    color = "dodgerblue" ,
    pch = 2 , 
    size = 4
  )

Update graph aesthetics based on variables

gg_base + 
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors, color = year),
    pch = 10
  )
